DESCRIPTION:Presented by Friends for Free Speech & Intellectual Diversity 
 at Duke ("Friends for Duke") and the Duke Civil Discourse Project. \n\nPa
 nelists: \nJAY BILAS (T'86\, Law'92) - Lead college basketball analyst fo
 r ESPN\nKEVIN WHITE - Renowned former athletic director at Duke\, Notre D
 ame\, Arizona State\, Tulane\, Maine\, and Loras College\nDORIANE LAMBELE
 T COLEMAN - Thomas L. Perkins Distinguished Professor Law\, Chair of Duke
 's Athletic Council\, Co-Director of Duke's Center for Sports Law and Pol
 icy\nPETER FEAVER - Professor of Political Science and Public Policy\, Di
 rector of Duke's Program in American Grand Strategy\, Chair of the "Acade
 mic Success" subcommittee on President's Task Force evaluating athletics 
 at Duke\nMILLIE MUIR (T'25\, MMS'26) - Duke Volleyball team captain\, all
  ACC academic team\, Duke Presidential Ambassador\, Duke representative t
 o the 2025-26 ACC Student Athletic Advisory Committee\n\nModerator: SUE W
 ASIOLEK (T'76\, M.H.A.'78\, LL.M'93) - "Dean Sue" is an Adjunct Professor
  in Duke's Civil Discourse Project and former Associate Vice President of
  Student Affairs and Dean of Students at Duke
