CREATED:20251125T210107Z
DESCRIPTION:Embark on a vibrant musical journey as the Duke Chinese Music 
 Ensemble presents A Tour of Ethnic and Opera Music\, an evening celebrati
 ng the breadth and beauty of China's diverse musical traditions. Led by t
 alented student performers and guided by expert Duke faculty member Jenni
 fer Chang\, the ensemble offers an immersive program that highlights both
  regional folk styles and the expressive drama of Chinese opera.\n\nThe c
 oncert showcases traditional instruments such as the erhu\, pipa\, guzhen
 g\, dizi\, and yangqin\, each bringing its own distinctive color and cult
 ural history. Through evocative melodies\, lush timbres\, and dynamic ens
 emble textures\, the program traces musical influences from across China'
 s many ethnic groups-revealing the depth\, variety\, and storytelling pow
 er of these living traditions.\n\nIn contrast\, selections from Chinese o
 pera present a world of expressive gesture\, heightened vocality\, and th
 eatrical flair. These pieces illuminate the artistry behind one of the wo
 rld's most enduring performance traditions\, capturing moments of heroism
 \, tenderness\, suspense\, and celebration.\n\nHeld in the intimate Nelso
 n Music Room\, the concert offers an up-close experience of music that is
  at once ancient and continually evolving. Whether you are familiar with 
 Chinese musical traditions or discovering them for the first time\, this 
 program invites you to explore a captivating sound world shaped by centur
 ies of cultural heritage.\n\nFree and open to the public. All are welcome
 .
DURATION:PT2H
DTSTAMP:20251125T210107Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260412T170000
LAST-MODIFIED:20251125T210107Z
