DESCRIPTION:Duke students are invited to meet Charity Tuseko Sindano (Exec
 utive Fellow at FUSE-City of Durham)-a seasoned water\, sanitation\, hygi
 ene and energy professional with 16+ years of experience across the USA\,
  UK and Africa-to learn about energy systems\, water management\, interna
 tional development\, and local initiatives in Durham\, NC. Dinner will be
  provided\; registration is required.\n\nHosted by the Global Energy Acce
 ss Network (GLEAN)\, an interdisciplinary network of graduate and undergr
 aduate students at Duke University. Sponsored by The James E. Rogers Ener
 gy Access Project at Duke University and the Nicholas Institute for Energ
 y\, Environment & Sustainability.\n\n<a href="https://nicholasinstitute.d
 uke.edu/events/exploring-energy-water-nexus-charity-tuseko-sindano">View 
 the speaker bio and register</a>.
DURATION:PT1H
